      • onWebSocketFailure

        default void onWebSocketFailure(Throwable t)
        Invoked when a web socket has been closed due to an error reading from or writing to the network. Both outgoing and incoming messages may have been lost. No further calls to this listener will be made.
        Parameters:
        t - failure reason

      • onWebSocketClosing

        default void onWebSocketClosing(int code,
                                String reason)
        Invoked when the remote peer has indicated that no more incoming messages will be transmitted.
        Parameters:
        code - status code for closing
        reason - reason for closing

      • onWebSocketClosed

        default void onWebSocketClosed(int code,
                               String reason)
        Invoked when both peers have indicated that no more messages will be transmitted and the connection has been successfully released. No further calls to this listener will be made.
        Parameters:
        code - status code for closing
        reason - reason for closing

      • onWebSocketOpen

        default void onWebSocketOpen(Response response)
        Invoked when a web socket has been accepted by the remote peer and may begin transmitting messages.
        Parameters:
        response - server response

      • onWebSocketMessage

        default void onWebSocketMessage(String json)
        Invoked with the unaltered json String when Asterisk sends a message.
        Parameters:
        json - original json from Asterisk
